  Source:
    Title: The Habit of Being
    Locus:
      Description: Letter to Alfred Corn
      Date: May 30, 1962
By: Flannery O'Connor
---
Faith rises and falls like the tides of an invisible sea. ... You realize,
I think, that it is more valuable, more mysterious, altogether more immense
than anything you can learn or decide upon in college.
